## Feature Flags

Flags are defined in `feature_flags.yaml` and injected as environment variables at deploy time.

| Flag | Default | Description |
|------|---------|-------------|
{% for flag in flags -%}
| `{{ flag }}` | OFF | — |
{% else -%}
| — | — | No flags yet. Run `ci_cd feature start {{ name }} <flag>` |
{% endfor %}

To activate a flag locally:
```bash
export FEATURE_<FLAG>=true
```

## Deployment

```bash
# Start a feature
ci_cd feature start {{ name }} <flag>

# Test in dev (flag ON)
ci_cd feature activate-dev {{ name }} <flag>

# Dark launch to prod (flag OFF)
ci_cd deploy prod {{ name }} <flag>

# Release to users
ci_cd release {{ name }} <flag>

# Rollback
ci_cd deactivate-prod {{ name }} <flag>
```

## Development Methodology

See `../../ci_cd/TBD_PRACTICES.md` for TBD/TDD/BDD guidelines.

- **TBD:** One branch (`main`). Feature flags hide incomplete work.
- **TDD:** Red → Green → Refactor.
- **BDD:** Gherkin scenarios in `tests/features/`.
